<paragraph id="E8403669FF88FFF4FF391E4585A8B669" blockId="31.[160,252,1096,1122]" box="[160,252,1096,1122]" pageId="31" pageNumber="830">
<heading id="B3088105FF88FFF4FF391E4585A8B669" bold="true" box="[160,252,1096,1122]" centered="true" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="31" pageNumber="830" reason="3">
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFF88FFF4FF391E4585A8B669" baseAuthorityName="Curran" baseAuthorityYear="1928" box="[160,252,1096,1122]" class="Insecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="830" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFF88FFF4FF391E4585A8B669" bold="true" box="[160,252,1096,1122]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="830">Diptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E8403669FF88FFF4FF391E708492B748" blockId="31.[160,1156,1149,1728]" pageId="31" pageNumber="830">
Aquatic flies are complex and amazingly diverse globally. The first inland aquatic invertebrate ever reported from the 
<collectingCountry id="90E876F9FF88FFF4FDEA1E928612B6B3" box="[627,838,1183,1208]" name="US Virgin Islands" pageId="31" pageNumber="830">US Virgin Islands</collectingCountry>
is the Ephydrid shorefly 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFF88FFF4FF391ECF86E9B6D0" authority="(Wiedemann, 1830) (Ale-Rocha and Mathis 2015)" authorityName="Ale-Rocha and Mathis" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="Wiedemann" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[160,957,1218,1243]" class="Insecta" family="Ephydridae" genus="Paralimna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="830" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thomae">
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFF88FFF4FF391ECF8426B6D0" box="[160,370,1218,1243]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="830">Paralimna thomae</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FF88FFF4FE1A1ECF8702B6D0" author="Wiedemann CRW" box="[387,598,1218,1243]" pageId="31" pageNumber="830" refId="ref31761" refString="Wiedemann CRW. 1830. Aussereuropaische zweiflugelige Insecten, Vol. 2. Hamm (GER): Schulz; p. 648." type="journal volume" year="1830">Wiedemann, 1830</bibRefCitation>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FF88FFF4FDF61ECF86E0B6D0" author="Ale-Rocha R &amp; Mathis WN" box="[623,948,1218,1243]" pageId="31" pageNumber="830" pagination="1 - 149" refId="ref22105" refString="Ale-Rocha R, Mathis WN. 2015. A revision of the New World species of Paralimna Loew (Diptera: Ephydridae). Smithson Contrib Zool. 643: 1 - 149." type="journal article" year="2015">Ale-Rocha and Mathis 2015</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. The flies of the 
<collectingCountry id="90E876F9FF88FFF4FF391EE88434B6F5" box="[160,352,1253,1278]" name="US Virgin Islands" pageId="31" pageNumber="830">US Virgin Islands</collectingCountry>
were first surveyed by 
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FF88FFF4FDE91EE8865FB6F5" author="Curran CH" box="[624,779,1253,1278]" pageId="31" pageNumber="830" pagination="1 - 118" refId="ref24134" refString="Curran CH. 1928. Insects of Porto Rico and the Virgin Islands: diptera or two-winged flies. Sci Surv Porto Rico Virgin Islands. 11: 1 - 118." type="journal article" year="1928">Curran (1928)</bibRefCitation>
and he reported several aquatic families, including 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFF88FFF4FE131F0A8779B72B" box="[394,557,1287,1312]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="830" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Chironomidae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFF88FFF4FDDB1F0A87F8B72B" authorityName=", Borkent and Spinelli" authorityYear="2007" box="[578,684,1287,1312]" class="Insecta" family="Culicidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="830" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Culicidae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFF88FFF4FD581F0A8610B72B" authorityName="Zetterstedt" authorityYear="1837" box="[705,836,1287,1312]" class="Insecta" family="Ephydridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="830" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Ephydridae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFF88FFF4FCC11F0A86ACB72B" box="[856,1016,1287,1312]" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="830" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Stratiomyidae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFF88FFF4FB941F0A81D5B72B" box="[1037,1153,1287,1312]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="830" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Syrphidae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFF88FFF4FF391F27844CB748" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[160,280,1322,1347]" class="Insecta" family="Tabanidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="830" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Tabanidae</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFF88FFF4FECE1F278496B748" box="[343,450,1322,1347]" class="Insecta" family="Tipulidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="830" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Tipulidae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A0E565E2FF88FFF4FF591F4085A0B4CB" pageId="31" pageNumber="830" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="E8403669FF88FFF4FF591F408615B43D" blockId="31.[160,1156,1149,1728]" pageId="31" pageNumber="830">
The 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFF88FFF4FF691F4084DBB76D" box="[240,399,1357,1382]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="830" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Chironomidae</taxonomicName>
of the US Virgin Islands were studied also by 
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FF88FFF4FC111F4081D0B76D" author="Curry LL &amp; Curry MC" box="[904,1156,1357,1382]" pageId="31" pageNumber="830" pagination="310 - 314" refId="ref24166" refString="Curry LL, Curry MC. 1971. The Chironomidae (Diptera) found in the US Virgin Islands and Anegada, British Virgin Islands. Can Entomol. 103 (3): 310 - 314. doi: 10.4039 / Ent 103310 - 3." type="journal article" year="1971">Curry and Curry (1971)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FF88FFF4FF481F628409B783" author="Miller AC" box="[209,349,1391,1416]" pageId="31" pageNumber="830" pagination="391 - 396" refId="ref27369" refString="Miller AC. 1971. Observations on the Chironomidae (Diptera) inhabiting the leaf axils of two species of Bromeliaceae on St. John, US Virgin Islands. Can Entomol. 103 (3): 391 - 396. doi: 10.4039 / Ent 103391 - 3." type="journal article" year="1971">Miller (1971)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FF88FFF4FEFE1F6287C7B783" author="Flemings MB &amp; Walsh RD" box="[359,659,1391,1416]" pageId="31" pageNumber="830" pagination="424 - 426" refId="ref24871" refString="Flemings MB, Walsh RD. 1966. The mosquitoes of the American Virgin Islands. Mosq News. 26: 424 - 426." type="journal article" year="1966">Flemings and Walsh (1966)</bibRefCitation>
reviewed the 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFF88FFF4FCA81F6285B2B7A0" authority=", Borkent and Spinelli (2007)" authorityName=", Borkent and Spinelli" authorityYear="2007" class="Insecta" family="Culicidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="830" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">
Culicidae, 
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FF88FFF4FC3A1F6285B2B7A0" author="Borkent A &amp; Spinelli GR" pageId="31" pageNumber="830" refId="ref22892" refString="Borkent A, Spinelli GR. 2007. Neotropical Ceratopogonidae (Diptera: Insecta). In: Adis J, Arias JR, Rueda-Delgado G, Wantzen KM, editors. Aquatic Biodiversity in Latin America (ABLA), Vol. 4. Sofia (BUL): Pensoft; p. 198." type="journal volume" year="2007">Borkent and Spinelli (2007)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
reviewed the 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFF88FFF4FE1C1F9F871FB7A0" box="[389,587,1426,1451]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="830" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Ceratopogonidae</taxonomicName>
, and 
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FF88FFF4FD1F1F9F8666B7A0" author="Fairchild GB" box="[646,818,1426,1451]" pageId="31" pageNumber="830" pagination="993 - 995" refId="ref24751" refString="Fairchild GB. 1966. The tabanid fauna of the West Indies. Proc First Int Congr Parasitol. 2: 993 - 995." type="journal article" year="1966">Fairchild (1966)</bibRefCitation>
reviewed the 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFF88FFF4FC481F9F811CB7A0" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[977,1096,1426,1451]" class="Insecta" family="Tabanidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="830" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Tabanidae</taxonomicName>
, with some Puerto Rico records from 
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FF88FFF4FE661FB887C3B7C5" author="Curran CH" box="[511,663,1461,1486]" pageId="31" pageNumber="830" pagination="1 - 118" refId="ref24134" refString="Curran CH. 1928. Insects of Porto Rico and the Virgin Islands: diptera or two-winged flies. Sci Surv Porto Rico Virgin Islands. 11: 1 - 118." type="journal article" year="1928">Curran (1928)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FF88FFF4FD561FB8811BB7C5" author="Medina Gaud S &amp; Martorell LF" box="[719,1103,1461,1486]" pageId="31" pageNumber="830" pagination="244 - 272" refId="ref27080" refString="Medina Gaud S, Martorell LF. 1974. The Insects of Caja de Muertos Island, Puerto Rico. J Agric Univ Puerto Rico. 58 (2): 244 - 272. doi: 10.46429 / jaupr. v 58 i 2.10684." type="journal article" year="1974">Medina Gaud and Martorell (1974)</bibRefCitation>
. The 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFF88FFF4FF391FDA846BB7FB" box="[160,319,1495,1520]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="830" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Chironomidae</taxonomicName>
of the 
<collectingCountry id="90E876F9FF88FFF4FE061FDA8487B7FB" box="[415,467,1495,1520]" name="Virgin Islands" pageId="31" pageNumber="830">USVI</collectingCountry>
include species in the genera 
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFF88FFF4FCDE1FDA811CB418" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="830">
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFF88FFF4FCDE1FDA8698B7FB" authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1803" box="[839,972,1495,1520]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Chironomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="830" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Chironomus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFF88FFF4FC451FDA812BB7FB" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1913" box="[988,1151,1495,1520]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Glyptotendipes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="830" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Glyptotendipes</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFF88FFF4FF391FF7846EB418" authorityName="Van der Wulp" authorityYear="1874" box="[160,314,1530,1555]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Metriocnemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="830" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Metriocnemus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFF88FFF4FED01FF784B6B418" box="[329,482,1530,1555]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Microtendipes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="830" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Microtendipes</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFF88FFF4FE691FF7872CB418" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1913" box="[496,632,1530,1555]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Nanocladius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="830" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Nanocladius</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFF88FFF4FD1E1FF78651B418" authorityName="Philippi" authorityYear="1865" box="[647,773,1530,1555]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Pentaneura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="830" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pentaneura</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFF88FFF4FC8A1FF786E1B418" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1921" box="[787,949,1530,1555]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Phaenopsectra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="830" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Phaenopsectra</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFF88FFF4FC5A1FF7811CB418" box="[963,1096,1530,1555]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Polypedilum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="830" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Polypedilum</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFF88FFF4FF391C108441B43D" authorityName="Wulp" authorityYear="1874" box="[160,277,1565,1590]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Tanytarsus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="830" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFF88FFF4FF391C108441B43D" box="[160,277,1565,1590]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="830">Tanytarsus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FF88FFF4FEBB1C1084FAB43D" author="Curran CH" box="[290,430,1565,1590]" pageId="31" pageNumber="830" pagination="1 - 118" refId="ref24134" refString="Curran CH. 1928. Insects of Porto Rico and the Virgin Islands: diptera or two-winged flies. Sci Surv Porto Rico Virgin Islands. 11: 1 - 118." type="journal article" year="1928">Curran 1928</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FF88FFF4FE221C1087FFB43D" author="Curry LL &amp; Curry MC" box="[443,683,1565,1590]" pageId="31" pageNumber="830" pagination="310 - 314" refId="ref24166" refString="Curry LL, Curry MC. 1971. The Chironomidae (Diptera) found in the US Virgin Islands and Anegada, British Virgin Islands. Can Entomol. 103 (3): 310 - 314. doi: 10.4039 / Ent 103310 - 3." type="journal article" year="1971">Curry and Curry 1971</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FF88FFF4FD211C108661B43D" author="Miller AC" box="[696,821,1565,1590]" pageId="31" pageNumber="830" pagination="391 - 396" refId="ref27369" refString="Miller AC. 1971. Observations on the Chironomidae (Diptera) inhabiting the leaf axils of two species of Bromeliaceae on St. John, US Virgin Islands. Can Entomol. 103 (3): 391 - 396. doi: 10.4039 / Ent 103391 - 3." type="journal article" year="1971">Miller 1971</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E8403669FF88FFF4FF591C3285A0B4CB" blockId="31.[160,1156,1149,1728]" pageId="31" pageNumber="830">
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FF88FFF4FF591C3284F5B453" author="Cazorla CG &amp; Marino PI &amp; Diaz F &amp; Campos RE" box="[192,417,1599,1624]" pageId="31" pageNumber="830" pagination="1 - 13" refId="ref23418" refString="Cazorla CG, Marino PI, Diaz F, Campos RE. 2018. Diversity of Ceratopogonidae (Diptera: Culicomorpha) from the Reserva Natural Integral Punta Lara (Buenos Aires, Argentina). Rev Soc Entomol Argent. 77 (3): 1 - 13. doi: 10.25085 / rsea. 770301." type="journal article" year="2018">Cazorla et al. (2018)</bibRefCitation>
report the ceratopogonids (biting midges) 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFF88FFF4FC0A1C328408B470" authority="(Winnertz, 1852)" baseAuthorityName="Winnertz" baseAuthorityYear="1852" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Bezzia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="830" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nobilis" subGenus="Bezzia">
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFF88FFF4FC0A1C32868CB453" box="[915,984,1599,1624]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="830">Bezzia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFF88FFF4FC711C328179B453" box="[1000,1069,1599,1624]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="830">Bezzia</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFF88FFF4FBA51C3281D7B453" box="[1084,1155,1599,1624]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="830">nobilis</emphasis>
(Winnertz, 1852)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFF88FFF4FE041C6F8694B470" authority="(Macafie, 1939)" baseAuthorityName="Macafie" baseAuthorityYear="1939" box="[413,960,1634,1659]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Forcipomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="830" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nana" subGenus="Thyridomyia">
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFF88FFF4FE041C6F8770B470" box="[413,548,1634,1659]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="830">Forcipomyia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFF88FFF4FDAC1C6F87E9B470" box="[565,701,1634,1659]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="830">Thyridomyia</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFF88FFF4FD561C6F865CB470" box="[719,776,1634,1659]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="830">nana</emphasis>
(Macafie, 1939)
</taxonomicName>
from the ‘Virgin Islands’, but it is unclear whether their records come from the 
<collectingCountry id="90E876F9FF88FFF4FC071C8886E9B495" box="[926,957,1669,1694]" name="United States of America" pageId="31" pageNumber="830">US</collectingCountry>
or 
<collectingCountry id="90E876F9FF88FFF4FC771C8885A4B4CB" name="British Virgin Islands" pageId="31" pageNumber="830">British Virgin Islands</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A0E565E2FFB7FFCBFF591A8386C1B1A9" pageId="32" pageNumber="831" type="description">
<paragraph id="E8403669FFB7FFCBFF591A838426B37C" blockId="32.[160,1156,142,930]" pageId="32" pageNumber="831">
The psychodid genus 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFFB7FFCBFE501A838709B2AC" authorityName="Satchell" authorityYear="1955" box="[457,605,142,167]" class="Insecta" family="Psychodidae" genus="Neurosystasis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="831" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFFB7FFCBFE501A838709B2AC" box="[457,605,142,167]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="831">Neurosystasis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has two species: 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFFB7FFCBFCAF1A8381D7B2AC" authority="(Satchell, 1955)" baseAuthorityName="Satchell" baseAuthorityYear="1955" box="[822,1155,142,167]" class="Insecta" family="Psychodidae" genus="Neurosystasis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="831" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="terminalis">
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFFB7FFCBFCAF1A838692B2AC" box="[822,966,142,167]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="831">N. terminalis</emphasis>
(Satchell, 1955)
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="90E876F9FFB7FFCBFF7C1ABC846BB2C1" box="[229,319,177,202]" name="Jamaica" pageId="32" pageNumber="831">Jamaica</collectingCountry>
and 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFFB7FFCBFE111ABC8783B2C1" authority="(Knab, 1914)" baseAuthorityName="Knab" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[392,727,177,202]" class="Insecta" family="Psychodidae" genus="Neurosystasis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="831" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amplipenna">
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFFB7FFCBFE111ABC8767B2C1" box="[392,563,177,202]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="831">N. amplipenna</emphasis>
(Knab, 1914)
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="90E876F9FFB7FFCBFCB31ABC863CB2C1" box="[810,872,177,202]" name="Cuba" pageId="32" pageNumber="831">Cuba</collectingCountry>
, with the later species breeding in bromeliad phytotelmata (
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FFB7FFCBFDF71AD986DBB2E6" author="Quate LW &amp; Brown BV" box="[622,911,212,237]" pageId="32" pageNumber="831" pagination="1 - 117" refId="ref28786" refString="Quate LW, Brown BV. 2004. Revision of neotropical Setomimini (Diptera: Psychodidae; Psychodinae). Contrib Sci (Los Angeles). 500: 1 - 117." type="journal article" year="2004">Quate and Brown 2004</bibRefCitation>
). Similarly, 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFFB7FFCBFBB91AD981D7B2E6" box="[1056,1155,212,237]" class="Insecta" family="Psychodidae" genus="Arisemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="831" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFFB7FFCBFBB91AD981D7B2E6" box="[1056,1155,212,237]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="831">Arisemus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has many species reported from the Caribbean (
<collectingCountry id="90E876F9FFB7FFCBFD651AFB8633B304" box="[764,871,246,271]" name="Bahamas" pageId="32" pageNumber="831">Bahamas</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="90E876F9FFB7FFCBFCE01AFB86E3B304" box="[889,951,246,271]" name="Cuba" pageId="32" pageNumber="831">Cuba</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="90E876F9FFB7FFCBFC511AFB8172B304" box="[968,1062,246,271]" name="Jamaica" pageId="32" pageNumber="831">Jamaica</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="90E876F9FFB7FFCBFBA11AFB8587B339" name="Puerto Rico" pageId="32" pageNumber="831">Puerto Rico</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFFB7FFCBFF7E1B14841FB339" baseAuthorityName="Ferrington and Saether" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[231,331,281,306]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bogidiellidae" genus="Stygogidiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="32" pageNumber="831" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lucia">St Lucia</taxonomicName>
, and 
<collectingCountry id="90E876F9FFB7FFCBFE021B14874DB339" box="[411,537,281,306]" name="Martinique" pageId="32" pageNumber="831">Martinique</collectingCountry>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFFB7FFCBFDF51B148136B339" authority="(Satchell, 1955)" baseAuthorityName="Satchell" baseAuthorityYear="1955" box="[620,1122,281,306]" class="Insecta" family="Psychodidae" genus="Australopericoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="831" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caudata">
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFFB7FFCBFDF51B1486CEB339" box="[620,922,281,306]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="831">Australopericoma caudata</emphasis>
(Satchell, 1955)
</taxonomicName>
is reported from 
<collectingCountry id="90E876F9FFB7FFCBFED61B3184F9B35E" box="[335,429,316,341]" name="Jamaica" pageId="32" pageNumber="831">Jamaica</collectingCountry>
. But as yet there are no records of any of these genera from the 
<collectingCountry id="90E876F9FFB7FFCBFF491B53843AB37C" box="[208,366,350,375]" name="Virgin Islands" pageId="32" pageNumber="831">Virgin Islands</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E8403669FFB7FFCBFF591B8C8755B156" blockId="32.[160,1156,142,930]" pageId="32" pageNumber="831">
Although there has been an understandable focus in the literature on medically important groups, surprisingly little else has been reported on the aquatic flies of the 
<collectingCountry id="90E876F9FFB7FFCBFBFC1BA98463B3D4" name="US Virgin Islands" pageId="32" pageNumber="831">US Virgin Islands</collectingCountry>
(e.g. 
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FFB7FFCBFEED1BCB8710B3D4" author="Kenney JL &amp; Burkhalter KL &amp; Scott ML &amp; McAllister J &amp; Lang FE &amp; Webster S &amp; Maduro DJ &amp; Johannes J &amp; Liburd A &amp; Mutebi JP" box="[372,580,454,479]" pageId="32" pageNumber="831" pagination="8 - 15" refId="ref26052" refString="Kenney JL, Burkhalter KL, Scott ML, McAllister J, Lang FE, Webster S, Maduro DJ, Johannes J, Liburd A, Mutebi JP. 2017. Entomological investigations during early stages of a chikungunya outbreak in the United States Virgin Islands, 2014. J Am Mosq Control Assoc. 33 (1): 8 - 15. doi: 10.2987 / 16 - 6619.1." type="journal article" year="2017">Kenney et al. 2017</bibRefCitation>
). According to the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention’s Arbovirus Catalogue (https://wwwn.cdc.gov/arbocat/ accessed 
<date id="9C4110A9FFB7FFCBFF39180184D3B02E" box="[160,391,524,549]" pageId="32" pageNumber="831" value="2020-12-31">31 December 2020</date>
), there are 59 mosquito transmitted viruses reported from the Caribbean Islands. Some 28 mosquito species are known from the 
<collectingCountry id="90E876F9FFB7FFCBFC7D182381D7B04C" box="[996,1155,558,583]" name="Virgin Islands" pageId="32" pageNumber="831">Virgin Islands</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FFB7FFCBFF3F185C8463B061" author="Curran CH" box="[166,311,593,618]" pageId="32" pageNumber="831" pagination="1 - 118" refId="ref24134" refString="Curran CH. 1928. Insects of Porto Rico and the Virgin Islands: diptera or two-winged flies. Sci Surv Porto Rico Virgin Islands. 11: 1 - 118." type="journal article" year="1928">Curran 1928</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FFB7FFCBFED1185C8743B061" author="Belkin JN &amp; Schick RX &amp; Heinemann SJ" box="[328,535,593,618]" pageId="32" pageNumber="831" pagination="1 - 97" refId="ref22582" refString="Belkin JN, Schick RX, Heinemann SJ. 1965. Mosquito studies. V. (Mosquito species originally described from Middle America). Contrib Am Entomol Inst. 1: 1 - 97." type="journal article" year="1965">Belkin et al. 1965</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FFB7FFCBFDB0185C8734B061" author="Belkin JN &amp; Heinemann SJ &amp; Page WA" box="[553,608,593,618]" pageId="32" pageNumber="831" pagination="1 - 458" refId="ref22549" refString="Belkin JN, Heinemann SJ, Page WA. 1970. The Culicidae of Jamaica (Mosquito studies. XXI). Contrib Am Entomol Inst. 6: 1 - 458." type="journal article" year="1970">1970</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FFB7FFCBFDE8185C86F5B061" author="Flemings MB &amp; Walsh RD" box="[625,929,593,618]" pageId="32" pageNumber="831" pagination="424 - 426" refId="ref24871" refString="Flemings MB, Walsh RD. 1966. The mosquitoes of the American Virgin Islands. Mosq News. 26: 424 - 426." type="journal article" year="1966">Flemings and Walsh 1966</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FFB7FFCBFC2A185C8164B061" author="Bram RA" box="[947,1072,593,618]" pageId="32" pageNumber="831" pagination="1 - 122" refId="ref23104" refString="Bram RA. 1967. Cassification of genus Culex subgenus Culex in the New World (Diptera: Culicidae). Proc US Nat Mus. 120 (3557): 1 - 122. doi: 10.5479 / si. 00963801.120 - 3557.1." type="journal article" year="1967">Bram 1967</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FFB7FFCBFBDB185C8583B086" author="Stone A" pageId="32" pageNumber="831" pagination="1 - 8" refId="ref30763" refString="Stone A. 1969. Bredin-Archbold-Smithsonian Biological Survey of Dominica: the Mosquitoes of Dominica (Diptera: Culicidae). Smithson Contrib Zool. 16: 1 - 8. doi: 10.5479 / si. 00810282.16." type="journal article" year="1969">Stone 1969</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FFB7FFCBFF7018798493B086" author="Kenney JL &amp; Burkhalter KL &amp; Scott ML &amp; McAllister J &amp; Lang FE &amp; Webster S &amp; Maduro DJ &amp; Johannes J &amp; Liburd A &amp; Mutebi JP" box="[233,455,628,653]" pageId="32" pageNumber="831" pagination="8 - 15" refId="ref26052" refString="Kenney JL, Burkhalter KL, Scott ML, McAllister J, Lang FE, Webster S, Maduro DJ, Johannes J, Liburd A, Mutebi JP. 2017. Entomological investigations during early stages of a chikungunya outbreak in the United States Virgin Islands, 2014. J Am Mosq Control Assoc. 33 (1): 8 - 15. doi: 10.2987 / 16 - 6619.1." type="journal article" year="2017">Kenney et al. 2017</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FFB7FFCBFE40187987F7B086" author="Seger KR &amp; Drummond A &amp; Delgado D &amp; Day CA &amp; Sither CB &amp; Soghigian J &amp; Wiegmann BM &amp; Reiskind MH &amp; Ellis BR &amp; Byrd BD" box="[473,675,628,653]" pageId="32" pageNumber="831" pagination="214 - 216" refId="ref29834" refString="Seger KR, Drummond A, Delgado D, Day CA, Sither CB, Soghigian J, Wiegmann BM, Reiskind MH, Ellis BR, Byrd BD. 2019. First record of Mansonia dyari from Saint Croix, United States Virgin Islands. J Am Mosq Control Assoc. 35 (3): 214 - 216. doi: 10.2987 / 19 - 6859.1." type="journal article" year="2019">Seger et al. 2019</bibRefCitation>
), but only a few are known to transmit diseases to humans. 
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FFB7FFCBFE0D189B87C9B0A4" author="Curry LL &amp; Curry MC" box="[404,669,662,687]" pageId="32" pageNumber="831" pagination="310 - 314" refId="ref24166" refString="Curry LL, Curry MC. 1971. The Chironomidae (Diptera) found in the US Virgin Islands and Anegada, British Virgin Islands. Can Entomol. 103 (3): 310 - 314. doi: 10.4039 / Ent 103310 - 3." type="journal article" year="1971">Curry and Curry (1971)</bibRefCitation>
also provide records of 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFFB7FFCBFC24189B811AB0A4" box="[957,1102,662,687]" class="Insecta" family="Chaoboridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="831" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Chaoboridae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFFB7FFCBFF3918B48431B0D9" box="[160,357,697,722]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="831" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Ceratopogonidae</taxonomicName>
from St. John and St. Croix, and 
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FFB7FFCBFD6618B48682B0D9" author="Belkin JN &amp; Schick RX &amp; Heinemann SJ" box="[767,982,697,722]" pageId="32" pageNumber="831" pagination="1 - 97" refId="ref22582" refString="Belkin JN, Schick RX, Heinemann SJ. 1965. Mosquito studies. V. (Mosquito species originally described from Middle America). Contrib Am Entomol Inst. 1: 1 - 97." type="journal article" year="1965">Belkin et al. (1965</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FFB7FFCBFC7118B4814BB0D9" author="Belkin JN &amp; Heinemann SJ &amp; Page WA" box="[1000,1055,697,722]" pageId="32" pageNumber="831" pagination="1 - 458" refId="ref22549" refString="Belkin JN, Heinemann SJ, Page WA. 1970. The Culicidae of Jamaica (Mosquito studies. XXI). Contrib Am Entomol Inst. 6: 1 - 458." type="journal article" year="1970">1970</bibRefCitation>
) discuss 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFFB7FFCBFF3918D185A0B0FE" box="[160,244,732,757]" class="Insecta" family="Dixidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="831" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Dixidae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFFB7FFCBFEAC18D18492B0FE" box="[309,454,732,757]" class="Insecta" family="Chaoboridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="831" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Chaoboridae</taxonomicName>
for the region. The 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFFB7FFCBFD2E18D18678B0FE" authorityName="Newman" authorityYear="1834" box="[695,812,732,757]" class="Insecta" family="Simuliidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="831" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Simuliidae</taxonomicName>
of the Neotropical bioregion were thoroughly reviewed and revised in 
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FFB7FFCBFDE718F3814DB11C" author="Coscaron S &amp; Coscaron Arias CL" box="[638,1049,766,791]" pageId="32" pageNumber="831" refId="ref23690" refString="Coscaron S, Coscaron Arias CL. 2007. Neotropical Simuliidae (Diptera: Insecta). In: Adis J, Arias JR, Rueda-Delgado G, Wantzen KM, editors. Aquatic Biodiversity in Latin America (ABLA), Vol. 3. Sofia (BUL): Pensoft; p. 685." type="journal volume" year="2007">Coscarón and Coscarón Arias (2007)</bibRefCitation>
, presenting only four species from 
<collectingCountry id="90E876F9FFB7FFCBFE44192C8730B131" box="[477,612,801,826]" name="Puerto Rico" pageId="32" pageNumber="831">Puerto Rico</collectingCountry>
, and none from the 
<collectingCountry id="90E876F9FFB7FFCBFCC0192C86A1B131" box="[857,1013,801,826]" name="Virgin Islands" pageId="32" pageNumber="831">Virgin Islands</collectingCountry>
; we suspect there are more species to find.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E8403669FFB7FFCBFF59196B86C1B1A9" blockId="32.[160,1156,142,930]" pageId="32" pageNumber="831">
Of the 18 aquatic dipteran families listed for 
<collectingCountry id="90E876F9FFB7FFCBFD56196B8606B174" box="[719,850,870,895]" name="Puerto Rico" pageId="32" pageNumber="831">Puerto Rico</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FFB7FFCBFC1A196B85B3B1A9" author="Gutierrez-Fonsec PE &amp; Rosas KG &amp; Ramirez A" pageId="32" pageNumber="831" pagination="215 - 219" refId="ref25397" refString="Gutierrez-Fonsec PE, Rosas KG, Ramirez A. 2013. Aquatic insects of Puerto Rico: a list of families. Dugesiana. 20 (2): 215 - 219." type="journal article" year="2013">Gutiérrez-Fonsec et al. (2013)</bibRefCitation>
, we found six families, plus two not mentioned in that work.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
